-- Daimler May Overtake VW in 2015 Luxury Cars, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 2012-04-29T16:06:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-29/daimler-may-overtake-vw-in-2015-luxury-cars-handelsblatt-says.html
Daimler AG (DAI) ’s Mercedes-Benz brand
may regain its position as the world’s second-largest of luxury
cars in 2015 after losing it to Audi, Handelsblatt reported
citing forecasts from the Center of Automotive Research at the
university of Duisburg-Essen.  According to the CAR forecasts, Bayerische Motoren Werke
will sell 1.76 million vehicles in 2015, followed by Mercedes
with 1.68 million and  Volkswagen AG (VOW) ’s Audi with 1.63 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Julie Cruz in Frankfurt at 
 jcruz6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
